TO DO List:
-----------

(1) .VBoxCLI

    Configuration file in home directory store VM# for virtual machines in.

(2) register auto [ --by-uuid | --by-name ]

    Automatic VM# configuration that sorts virtual machines by UUID or Name and
    writes the VM# list into the .VBoxCLI configuration file. Default is sort
    by name.

(3) register set <uuid> <vm#>

    Manual VM# configuration that stores user's settings into .VBoxCLI
    configuration file.

(4) No VM# warning

    Warn when one or more virtual machines have no VM#. Suggest to run
    automatic or manual numbering. Error message when none of the machines are
    numbered.

(5) README.md

    Compose a README.md file for github once we are ready to export the project
    there.

(6) Create and enhance more commands:

    - shutdown (acpi button)
    - poweroff
    - ls -r (list running vms)
    - info <VM#> (take output from "VBoxManage showvminfo <uuid> --machinereadable"
     and present in tabular form)
